Package: linux-diagnostics
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         python3 (>= 3.11),
         python3-venv,
         python3-pip
Description: Always-on diagnostics daemon for Linux NFS and SMB filesystems
 Always-on Diagnostics daemon for monitoring Linux NFS and SMB anomalies
 and automatic log-collection.
 .
 The daemon is installed under /opt/linux_diagnostics and runs from a
 self-contained Python virtual environment built at install time.
 Configuration lives in /etc/linux_diagnostics/config.yaml; the output
 directory is user-tunable via the aod_output_dir key in that file and
 is created by the daemon on first use.